==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Melancholic
<hw>Mel"an*chol`ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>melancholicus</ets>, Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧lancholique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Given to melancholy;
depressed; melancholy; dejected; unhappy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Just as the <qex>melancholic</qex> eye⟦br⟧
Sees fleets and armies in the sky.</q> <rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melancholic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Melancholic
<hw>Mel"an*chol`ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One affected with a gloomy state of mind.</def> <rj><au>J.
Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gloomy state of mind; melancholy.</def>
<rj><au>Clarendon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melancholily</ent>⟦br⟧
